# graphify (project)

If `graphify-out/graph.json` exists, use it **first** for architecture, module relationship, and “how does X connect to Y” questions:

```bash
graphify query "<question>"
graphify path "A" "B"
graphify explain "NodeLabel"
```

If the graph is missing, follow `docs/agents/graphify.md` to build (`graphify extract . --code-only --out .`). Do not invent edges. Prefer domain terms from `docs/agents/domain.md`: user, role, permission, role group, permission group.

This does not replace MkDocs or runtime application behavior.
